Chelsea will play Liverpool in the final of this season’s FA Cup. The Blues beat Crystal Palace 2-0 in the second semi-final of the competition at Wembley on Sunday. Ruben Loftus-Cheek and Mason Mount netted two second-half goals to seal the win. Thomas Tuchel’s men will now take on Liverpool for the second domestic title in England. The Reds qualified for the final with a 3-2 victory over Manchester City on Saturday. Jurgen Klopp’s men have already won the Carabao Cup this season and are chasing an unprecedented quadruple.